---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Hieroglyphs">
  <article class="space-y-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary mb-8">Hieroglyphs</h1>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed"><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Plain-text project management for indie developers</strong></p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Hieroglyphs is a native macOS SwiftUI app that brings simplicity and ownership to project management. Instead of complex web-based tools with subscriptions and lock-in, Hieroglyphs uses a filesystem-based approach: your projects live in directories as markdown files with YAML frontmatter.</p>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Your data stays on your machine, in plain text, under your control. Version it with git, back it up however you want, edit it with any tool you choose. Hieroglyphs provides a beautiful native interface to manage this data, but the files remain yours.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">Key Concepts</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary ml-4">
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Projects</strong>: Top-level containers for related work, living in their own directories</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Cards</strong>: Individual work items (bugs, features, tasks) with status, priority, and type tracked in YAML frontmatter</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Plans</strong>: Bounded units of work containing multiple cards, representing sprints or milestones</li>
        <li><strong class="font-semibold text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary">Plain text</strong>: Everything is markdown and YAML, no proprietary formats or databases</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">Open Source</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary leading-relaxed">Hieroglyphs is open source and available on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/adamrdrew/hieroglyphs" class="text-accent-primary dark:text-accent-dark-primary hover:underline">github.com/adamrdrew/hieroglyphs</a></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
